World oil prices fell despite a new hurricane approaching the Gulf of Mexico.
OPEC pledged to increase crude supply by two million barrels per day from October 1 if needed.
Hurricane Rita strengthened to a category two storm with winds of 160 km/h.
Evacuations were underway in Louisiana and Texas as Rita threatened the Gulf Coast.
Governor Blanco declared a state of emergency in western Louisiana.
Galveston County ordered mandatory evacuations starting Wednesday.
Shelters were prepared in nearby towns, and preparations were made to protect New Orleans from potential flooding.
Rita is the 17th named storm of the Atlantic hurricane season.
